[I] ROCm Systems Profiler: Application Profiling, Tracing, and Analysis

[T] ROCm Systems Profiler (rocprofiler-systems), formerly Omnitrace, is a
[T] comprehensive profiling and tracing tool for parallel applications written
[T] in C, C++, Fortran, HIP, OpenCL, and Python which execute on the CPU or
[T] CPU+GPU. It is capable of gathering the performance information of
[T] functions through any combination of binary instrumentation, call-stack
[T] sampling, user-defined regions, and Python interpreter hooks.

[U] https://github.com/ROCm/rocprofiler-systems

[A] Advanced Micro Devices, Inc.
